               <head>Translation of Mishkat-i sharif, vol. 3</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Tarjumah-'i Mishkāt-i sharīf by Muḥammad ibn ʿAbd Allāh al-Khaṭīb al-Tabrīzī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2007003439 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh91004955" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3718-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Large portion from the Persian translation and commentary on the Mishkāt al-maṣābīḥ by ʿAbd al-Ḥaqq ibn Sayf al-Dīn Dihlavī, known as the muḥaddis̲, usually entitled <title>Ashiʿat al-lamaʿāt fī sharḥ al-Mishkāt</title> by Muḥammad ibn ʿAbd Allāh al-Khaṭīb al-Tabrīzī, completed 1616
                        </p>
                        <p>Consists of the third volume, extending from kitāb al-buyūʿ to kitāb al-ruʾyā
</p>
                        <p>Text is prefixed with a list of contents
</p>
                        <p>Poor condition
</p>
                        <p>Boards delaminating, exposing inner fabric consisting of sheets of text, including accounts, letters, language exercises, and more
</p>
                        <p>Boards show indications that the manuscript hay be related to the Delhi Persian Collection
</p>
                        <p>Annotated throughout; notes on f. 258v end with the name Qāz̤ī Muḥammad S̲anāʾ Allāh
</p>
                        <p>Not dated
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian &amp; Arabic</textLang>
